In a speech at One Police Plaza in New York City, President Biden expressed his gratitude to law enforcement and highlighted the importance of community policing. He honored Detective Wilbert Mora and Jason Rivera, who were killed in the line of duty, and called for stricter gun control measures. Biden emphasized the need for funding for community policing, violence intervention programs, and mental health services. He also discussed the crackdown on ghost guns and gun trafficking. The President urged Congress to pass universal background checks, ban assault weapons, and hold gun manufacturers accountable. He ended by emphasizing the importance of working together to keep communities safe.